en_58119_0	The Passing out Parade (PoP) of 98 recruits of the Sri Lanka Corps of Military Police (SLCMP), 03 recruits of the Sri Lanka National Guard and 01 Sri Lanka Army Pioneer Corps who followed the SLCMP Recruit Training Course 2019 - 1 took place recently at the SLCMP Training School in Giritale.
en_58119_1	Brigadier E.R.P Weerawardena, Director Assets Management, participated as the Chief Guest and received the salute of the recruits who passed out after their three-month long training.
en_58119_2	Special merit awards were also awarded to following categories under different fields of excellence on the same occasion.
en_58119_3	Second Lieutenant S.P.A.S Dissanayake was adjudged as the Best Platoon Commander.
en_58119_4	The trophy for the Best Platoon Sergeant went to Staff Sergeant K.R.G.D Weerasinghe while the Best Section Commander trophy was won by Corporal H.M.M.S Abeyratne Banda.
en_58119_5	Corporal S.M.B Dissanayake was selected as the Best Physical Training Instructor and Private R.M.C.D Rathnayake was awarded as the Best All Rounder.
en_58119_6	Meanwhile, Private E.M.A.M Weerakoon was awarded as the Best Shooter.
en_58119_7	The POP at Giritale was attended by Senior Officers, parents and invitees.
